![](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2011/09/weechat_logo.png?w=150 "weechat_logo")

WeeChat supports encrypted IRC connections using GnuTLS. For FreeBSD's port of WeeChat, as root:`
# cd /usr/ports/irc/weechat
# make
[select GnuTLS]
# make install
`

<!--more-->

In WeeChat:`
/set weechat.network.gnutls_ca_file "/usr/local/share/certs/ca-root-nss.crt"
/set irc.server.freenode.addresses "chat.freenode.net/7000"
/set irc.server.freenode.ssl on
/set irc.server.freenode.ssl_dhkey_size 1024
/connect freenode
`

_NB:_ WeeChat's support for GnuTLS is rather flaky, with numerous bug reports recently surfacing on the net ([one such example](http://securityvulns.com/Zdocument866.html)). WeeChat's [FAQ](http://www.weechat.org/files/doc/weechat_faq.en.html#irc_ssl_connection) suggests disabling verification of secure connections with:`
/set irc.server.freenode.ssl_verify off`